HEADWORD: Incumbrancer
<hw>In*cum"bran*cer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>One who holds an incumbrance, or some legal claim, lien, or charge
on an estate.</def> <rj><au>Kent.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

